Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
extract_shrink_factor(25.10)                      extract_shrink_factor(25.10)

Name
       extract_shrink_factor

Syntax
        extract_shrink_factor <shrink_factor_value>

       Type: Double

       Default: 1.0

       Specifies  the  shrink  factor by which to shrink the design before ex-
       traction. The shrink factor is used only for  extraction  calculations.
       It does not change the actual design.

       This global variable must only be used when restoring design.

       Note:  This  global  is  not  recommended  for newer technologies where
       shrink factor is defined in the Quantus techfiles  or  capacitance  ta-
       bles.

       To set this global, use the set command.

Example
              * The following global variable sets the shrink factor to 0.9:

                set extract_shrink_factor 0.9

                Setting  the  shrink  factor  to  0.9  means the value of wire
                lengths, widths, and spacings in the design will shrink to 90%
                of their original values.

